- "garden of elementary knowledge" refers to the wide array of easy questions;
- "blossoms of basic recall" represent questions requiring a recall cognitive level;
- "plucking from the vine" symbolizes the selection process of these questions;
- "measure of simplicity" refers to the difficulty level of the questions, specifically 'easy'.

